    "what_description": "Kadua elatior is a species of flowering plant in the family Rubiaceae, native to Hawaii. It is a shrub or small tree, 2-5 meters in height, with glabrous to pubescent stems. The leaves are opposite, elliptic to ovate, 6-20 cm long, and 2-8 cm wide, with a petiole 1-4 mm long. The inflorescence is a corymb with 1-3 flowers, each flower having a calyx of 4 sepals 1-2 mm long and a corolla of 4 petals 2-5 mm long. The flowers are yellow or white, with 4 stamens and a superior ovary containing 4-8 seeds.",
