    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Kadua elatior are infusion, tea, tincture, salve, and decoction. Infusion is a liquid extract made by steeping the leaves in hot water, used to treat fever, rheumatism, and skin conditions. A decoction is a more potent liquid made by boiling the leaves in water, used to treat digestive issues and menstrual problems. Tincture is a concentrated liquid extract made by soaking the leaves in a solvent, used to treat anxiety, insomnia, and respiratory issues. A salve is a topical preparation made by mixing the leaves with a carrier oil, used to treat skin conditions, wounds, and inflammation.",
